2 To continue the Clean Water Task Force to study the public water system in Shreveport and
3 report its findings no later than November 18, 2026.
4 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Department of Health implemented the Safe Drinking
5 Water Program that provides comprehensive drinking water protection to the citizens and
6 visitors of Louisiana, supervising over a thousand public water systems for compliance with
7 state and federal drinking water regulations; and
8 WHEREAS, the goal of the Safe Water Drinking Program is to prevent illness and
9 death that can occur from waterborne disease outbreaks or chemical exposure associated
10 with contaminated drinking water; and
11 WHEREAS, the Safe Drinking Water Program monitors collection, analysis, and
12 review of bacteriological and chemical samples to ensure compliance with maximum
13 contaminant levels, treatment technique requirements, monitoring and analytical
14 requirements; and
15 WHEREAS, the Safe Drinking Water Program conducts sanitary surveys and site
16 inspections to evaluate the capability of a drinking water system to consistently and reliably
17 deliver an adequate quality and quantity of safe drinking water to the consumer and to ensure
18 compliance with state and federal drinking water regulations; and
19 WHEREAS, Shreveport's water system has been facing a series of issues, including
20 a failing grade for the third consecutive year due to aging infrastructure, manganese levels,
21 and algae blooms; and
