HR 367 Original 2026 Regular Session Walters
Continues the Clean Water Task Force to study the public water system in Shreveport and
report its findings no later than Nov. 18, 2026.
Requires the task force to hold both meetings and public hearings monthly and submit a
written report of findings and recommendations to the House Committee on Health and
Welfare.
Requires the task force to assess the condition of existing water infrastructure, review water
quality reports, analyze water utility management practices, and identify funding gaps and
potential state and federal funding options.
